      "writtenOn": "2018-05-16T20:52:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think a enum of some kind makes sense.\n\nThe thing I\u0027m a little stuck on is if the texture is luminance do we want the client to explicitly say luminance or should they use any of R, G, B? At first I was thinking luminance but in a shader you access that value using .r, .g, or .b. On the other hand, we already have the idea of \"gray\" as a SkColorType where gray pretty much means luminance. Maybe we stick with a RGBA enum and can revist when we get around to supporting luminance textures?\n\nI\u0027d add a new enum rather than exposing something from one of the private types. When this stabilizes maybe we redefine those private types around the new public enum.\n\nApologies for bike shedding.",
      "parentUuid": "a5d98470_9938c5fe",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 230,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 230,
        "endChar": 16
